00:32:29,194 --> 00:32:33,130
But I did,
while you were gone,

500
00:32:33,164 --> 00:32:35,860
jot this down for you.

501
00:32:39,738 --> 00:32:41,569
Wait, you just happened
to remember it?

502
00:32:41,606 --> 00:32:45,303
I'd appreciate it
if you ran it.

503
00:32:45,343 --> 00:32:48,141
I'll see
what I can do.

504
00:32:48,179 --> 00:32:51,910
In the meantime, is there anybody
else I could talk to?

505
00:32:51,950 --> 00:32:54,714
Anybody who knew
he'd be here today?

506
00:32:54,753 --> 00:32:57,745
- What about family?
- Ooh! His mother.

507
00:32:57,789 --> 00:33:00,485
She lives in Florida,

508
00:33:00,525 --> 00:33:03,858
but he was gonna put her number
into my phone in case of an emergency.

509
00:33:03,895 --> 00:33:07,194
I just totally forgot.

510
00:33:07,232 --> 00:33:09,132
Thank you.

511
00:33:09,167 --> 00:33:12,034
Okay.

512
00:33:12,070 --> 00:33:15,062
Wait.

513
00:33:17,108 --> 00:33:20,703
The number you have reached
is not in service at this time.

514
00:33:20,745 --> 00:33:22,610
- There is no new number.
- No luck.

515
00:33:22,647 --> 00:33:26,083
He must have input
a wrong digit.

516
00:33:26,117 --> 00:33:28,642
He's always been bad
electronically.

517
00:33:34,059 --> 00:33:35,890
Shoot!

518
00:33:35,927 --> 00:33:39,454
You need proof.
You need some sort of evidence

519
00:33:39,497 --> 00:33:42,796
that this is real,
that he actually exists,

520
00:33:42,834 --> 00:33:44,529
don't you?

521
00:33:47,706 --> 00:33:50,732
- Antidepressants.
- I, uh-

522
00:33:50,775 --> 00:33:53,505
I have a prescription
for that, so...

523
00:33:53,545 --> 00:33:56,275
Holloway: That kind of
says it all, doesn't it?

524
00:33:56,314 --> 00:33:58,407
Please hand that to me.

525
00:34:00,085 --> 00:34:02,883
I'll be right back,
Mr. Holloway.

526
00:34:02,921 --> 00:34:05,048
Where are you going?

527
00:34:06,991 --> 00:34:09,824
May I have
my medication back, please?

528
00:34:17,369 --> 00:34:19,360
Detective Franklin,

529
00:34:19,404 --> 00:34:21,736
we have people here
she can talk to.

530
00:34:21,773 --> 00:34:24,367
I'm sure Miss Markham
could arrange something.

531
00:34:26,311 --> 00:34:29,075
All right, I'll run
the Social. I'll be back.

532
00:34:29,114 --> 00:34:32,641
You got it.

533
00:34:46,564 --> 00:34:48,623
Come on.

534
00:35:20,765 --> 00:35:22,460
- Wait wait.
- Just stay out of the way.

535
00:35:22,500 --> 00:35:25,401
Come on.
Your brace.

536
00:35:25,437 --> 00:35:27,405
Do you want your bag?

537
00:35:27,439 --> 00:35:29,430
No, just leave it
in the back. That's fine.

538
00:35:47,892 --> 00:35:49,883
Thank God.

539
00:36:00,472 --> 00:36:02,463
Where is it?

540
00:36:05,243 --> 00:36:07,939
Okay, wanna come
upstairs now?

541
00:36:07,979 --> 00:36:09,970
Shoot!

542
00:36:13,651 --> 00:36:16,643
Holloway:
It's not under the seat.

543
00:36:16,688 --> 00:36:18,417
Shoot!

544
00:36:19,757 --> 00:36:22,021
Wanna come upstairs now?

545
00:36:22,060 --> 00:36:24,790
- It's not here.
- What's not here?

546
00:36:24,829 --> 00:36:27,229
His bag. It has
his computer in it,

547
00:36:27,265 --> 00:36:30,666
all of his information-
everything.

548
00:36:30,702 --> 00:36:32,932
Somebody had to have
gotten into the car.

549
00:36:32,971 --> 00:36:35,201
What makes you think that?

550
00:36:35,240 --> 00:36:37,970
Because the bag was here
this morning. Now it's not.

551
00:36:38,009 --> 00:36:41,206
- It was right there.
- Miss Walsh, we need to speak with you.

552
00:36:41,246 --> 00:36:42,838
Now.

553
00:36:42,881 --> 00:36:45,042
I have the only set of keys.

554
00:36:45,083 --> 00:36:47,551
Now.

555
00:36:56,127 --> 00:36:58,994
We're in the middle
of a huge transition.

556
00:36:59,030 --> 00:37:01,794
I've got patients to move,
equipment to transport.

557
00:37:01,833 --> 00:37:04,301
Every minute that I
or my security team

558
00:37:04,335 --> 00:37:07,270
spends chasing phantoms
on surveillance cameras

559
00:37:07,305 --> 00:37:10,206
or finding you trespassing
in a restricted area is one less minute

560
00:37:10,241 --> 00:37:12,209
we're able to do our jobs.

561
00:37:12,243 --> 00:37:15,110
Every minute you don't spending
looking for Kevin is a minute wasted.

562
00:37:15,146 --> 00:37:18,206
Mary, I checked seven
floors of this building.

563
00:37:18,249 --> 00:37:20,513
I checked with every
nurse's station.

564
00:37:20,552 --> 00:37:23,521
I checked the emergency room.
I checked the intensive care ward.

565
00:37:23,555 --> 00:37:25,614
What about the wing
that's being renovated?

566
00:37:25,657 --> 00:37:27,522
Franklin: Yes.

567
00:37:27,559 --> 00:37:29,959
- And?
- And no one

568
00:37:29,994 --> 00:37:31,791
reported seeing
your boyfriend.

569
00:37:31,829 --> 00:37:34,730
No one can even confirm that
he was in this hospital.

570
00:37:34,766 --> 00:37:36,961
Just what do you suppose
happened to him?

571
00:37:37,001 --> 00:37:39,196
- I don't know.
- Holloway: Look, there are 23 exits

572
00:37:39,237 --> 00:37:42,673
in this facility.
Six are manned by my men.

573
00:37:42,707 --> 00:37:45,608
Eight are alarmed and the rest are
carefully monitored by cameras.

574
00:37:45,643 --> 00:37:47,873
If anyone left this building

575
00:37:47,912 --> 00:37:49,743
under any manner
of duress

576
00:37:49,781 --> 00:37:51,510
we would know about it.

577
00:37:51,549 --> 00:37:54,211
Well, obviously, you're not
looking hard enough.

578
00:37:56,955 --> 00:38:00,413
- Detective...
- Detective Franklin.

579
00:38:01,759 --> 00:38:04,751
- Detective, who is it?
- Really?

580
00:38:04,796 --> 00:38:08,425
Okay, thank you.

581
00:38:08,466 --> 00:38:10,058
What did they say?

582
00:38:10,101 --> 00:38:13,229
We ran the Social Security number
you gave me.

583
00:38:13,271 --> 00:38:16,138
Good, okay,
what's the next step?

584
00:38:16,174 --> 00:38:19,337
It belongs to a 50-year-old
African-American woman.

585
00:38:19,377 --> 00:38:22,972
Well, that's obviously
a mistake.

586
00:38:23,014 --> 00:38:24,345
Not ours.

587
00:38:24,382 --> 00:38:25,974
I ran the number
you gave us.

588
00:38:26,017 --> 00:38:29,282
No, that's impossible.

589
00:38:29,320 --> 00:38:31,288
Okay, run them
again, please?

590
00:38:31,322 --> 00:38:33,347
Dr. Bensley,
thank you for joining us.

591
00:38:33,391 --> 00:38:35,359
I'd like to introduce you
to someone.

592
00:38:35,393 --> 00:38:38,988
- Hello, Mary.
- Hello.

593
00:38:39,030 --> 00:38:41,999
Markham: Dr. Bensley is our
hospital psychiatrist.

594
00:38:42,033 --> 00:38:44,126
I don't need
a psychiatrist.

595
00:38:44,168 --> 00:38:46,136
Did you get the prescription
I sent over?

596
00:38:46,170 --> 00:38:48,934
I did. Quite a
potent dosage, Mary.

597
00:38:48,973 --> 00:38:51,771
Would you mind coming
with me for a moment?

598
00:38:51,809 --> 00:38:53,606
Yes, actually, I would.

599
00:38:53,645 --> 00:38:57,274
It doesn't need to be
voluntary, Miss Walsh.

600
00:38:57,315 --> 00:39:00,250
Excuse me.
Excuse me!

601
00:39:00,284 --> 00:39:02,343
Right this way, please.

602
00:39:02,387 --> 00:39:04,787
This way.

603
00:39:04,822 --> 00:39:07,552
- Okay.
- Come on.

604
00:39:21,239 --> 00:39:25,005
So you've been treated for psychiatric
issues before, hmm, Mary?

605
00:39:27,478 --> 00:39:29,912
Answer the question,
Miss Walsh.

606
00:39:30,048 --> 00:39:31,982
I...

607
00:39:33,518 --> 00:39:37,352
I checked myself in
when I was 22.

608
00:39:39,791 --> 00:39:42,726
I was in grad school.
I was under a lot of stress.

609
00:39:42,760 --> 00:39:45,729
I was there for three days.
That's it.

610
00:39:45,763 --> 00:39:48,027
I don't see how
that's relevant.

611
00:39:48,066 --> 00:39:51,502
What are you doing
on antidepressants?

612
00:39:51,536 --> 00:39:53,970
Oh, you think
I'm making this up.

613
00:39:55,139 --> 00:39:57,699
You think that,

614
00:39:57,742 --> 00:40:00,711
what, my imaginary
boyfriend went missing?

615
00:40:00,745 --> 00:40:02,679
You're an only child.

616
00:40:02,714 --> 00:40:04,409
Your father left
when you were young.

617
00:40:04,449 --> 00:40:07,907
Your mother died
earlier this year

618
00:40:07,952 --> 00:40:09,715
in a hospital.

619
00:40:09,754 --> 00:40:13,155
Yes, February.

620
00:40:13,191 --> 00:40:16,251
She went in
for a routine check-up

621
00:40:16,294 --> 00:40:18,057
and never checked out.

622
00:40:18,096 --> 00:40:20,564
She had a blood infection.

623
00:40:20,598 --> 00:40:22,930
So it's not surprising
that your subconscious

624
00:40:22,967 --> 00:40:25,731
would choose a hospital
to fabricate-

625
00:40:25,770 --> 00:40:29,206
It's not my subconscious
anything.

626
00:40:29,240 --> 00:40:31,071
Oh my Lord!

627
00:40:31,109 --> 00:40:33,634
This is real.

628
00:40:36,047 --> 00:40:38,572
He was there for me.

629
00:40:38,616 --> 00:40:41,551
You know, I remember
her funeral.

630
00:40:41,586 --> 00:40:44,316
- He was at it.
- Kevin?

631
00:40:44,355 --> 00:40:46,323
Yes, Kevin.

632
00:40:46,357 --> 00:40:49,952
I know it's hard to lose somebody
you care deeply about, Mary.

633
00:40:49,994 --> 00:40:52,656
It's very understandable
how someone in your situation

634
00:40:52,697 --> 00:40:54,494
could suffer
a psychological break.

635
00:40:54,532 --> 00:40:56,397
You work long hours.

636
00:40:56,434 --> 00:40:58,493
You've lost your emotional
support system. You're alone.

637
00:40:58,536 --> 00:41:00,504
It's only natural for the brain
to reach for something,

638
00:41:00,538 --> 00:41:02,165
anything, to grab onto.

639
00:41:02,206 --> 00:41:04,401
He drove us here.

640
00:41:04,442 --> 00:41:05,966
He did.

641
00:41:06,010 --> 00:41:09,639
And I remember the ride
like the back of my hand.

642
00:41:09,680 --> 00:41:11,978
He- he- he was-

643
00:41:12,016 --> 00:41:14,143
He was chewing on the lid
of his coffee cup.

644
00:41:14,185 --> 00:41:17,951
- It's this little nervous habit that he has.
- Sorry.

645
00:41:17,989 --> 00:41:19,456
I know that it all
must seem real.

646
00:41:19,490 --> 00:41:21,822
It seems real
because it is real!

647
00:41:23,094 --> 00:41:26,621
I remember walking through
the parking structure.

648
00:41:26,664 --> 00:41:29,758
Memory is a very vivid
and powerful sensation, Mary.

649
00:41:29,801 --> 00:41:31,268
It is real!

650
00:41:31,302 --> 00:41:33,634
This whole situation
is real.

651
00:41:33,671 --> 00:41:36,105
And he's here.
He was here,

652
00:41:36,140 --> 00:41:39,405
He's somewhere
right now in this hospital

653
00:41:39,443 --> 00:41:41,638
and we're wasting time!

654
00:41:43,214 --> 00:41:46,581
The nurse advised me
to get coffee,

655
00:41:46,617 --> 00:41:48,778
said the surgery
would be an hour.

656
00:41:48,820 --> 00:41:52,256
It was 25 minutes,
and he's gone.

657
00:41:53,591 --> 00:41:55,058
It was real.

658
00:41:55,092 --> 00:41:57,356
It's all right, Mary.

659
00:41:57,395 --> 00:41:59,363
Can I just have
a moment alone?

660
00:41:59,397 --> 00:42:01,365
Take all the time
you need, dear.

661
00:42:01,399 --> 00:42:03,594
I'll be in my office
next door.

662
00:42:03,634 --> 00:42:05,727
Okay.

663
00:42:56,654 --> 00:42:58,747
Mary, I-

664
00:43:03,160 --> 00:43:05,458
Security.

665
00:43:37,561 --> 00:43:39,552
Want some company?

666
00:43:47,538 --> 00:43:50,905
Do you know I was just here
for a checkup today?

667
00:43:52,643 --> 00:43:54,804
Doctor told me I need
to take it easy.

668
00:43:57,148 --> 00:43:58,843
Then you call.

669
00:43:58,883 --> 00:44:02,546
I gotta tell you, this job can really
take its toll on you-

670
00:44:03,654 --> 00:44:05,645
your health,
your marriage.

671
00:44:05,690 --> 00:44:07,157
You're married?

672
00:44:07,191 --> 00:44:10,422
Was.

673
00:44:10,461 --> 00:44:13,828
Marriage, it can be
a funny thing, you know?

674
00:44:13,864 --> 00:44:17,322
You commit yourself,
you hand your heart over to someone,

675
00:44:17,368 --> 00:44:21,270
but it always seems like
it's the little things

676
00:44:21,305 --> 00:44:23,830
that keep
chipping away at it-

677
00:44:23,874 --> 00:44:26,399
Little disagreements.

678
00:44:26,444 --> 00:44:28,435
She-

679
00:44:28,479 --> 00:44:30,913
she hated the fact
that I was a cop.

680
00:44:30,948 --> 00:44:33,246
And you know what?

681
00:44:33,284 --> 00:44:36,185
Maybe-
maybe she was right.

682
00:44:36,220 --> 00:44:37,710
I don't know.

683
00:44:40,257 --> 00:44:43,715
I was working a gang shooting
over in Glassell Park,

684
00:44:43,761 --> 00:44:46,389
and my partner and I,

685
00:44:46,430 --> 00:44:48,898
we traced the shooter back
to his girlfriend's house.

686
00:44:48,933 --> 00:44:52,425
He'd been shacking up there
for a couple of weeks.

687
00:44:53,504 --> 00:44:55,472
And we had the kid cornered,
so we went in.

688
00:44:55,506 --> 00:44:58,168
He was unarmed,
gave himself right up.

689
00:45:02,713 --> 00:45:06,479
What we didn't know that his girlfriend
was in the house.

690
00:45:13,524 --> 00:45:16,550
The last thing I remember
before I blacked out...

691
00:45:19,497 --> 00:45:21,522
was watching my partner...

692
00:45:24,101 --> 00:45:26,899
his dark lifeless eyes

693
00:45:26,937 --> 00:45:29,030
as he fell to the floor.

694
00:45:37,848 --> 00:45:39,372
Now look at me.

695
00:45:39,417 --> 00:45:41,749
I've got a desk job
and high blood pressure

696
00:45:41,786 --> 00:45:45,517
and a doctor telling me
how to live my life.

697
00:45:45,556 --> 00:45:48,024
What I'm-

698
00:45:48,059 --> 00:45:50,050
what I'm trying
to say here is that...

699
00:45:53,064 --> 00:45:56,329
I understand what
you're going through.

700
00:46:01,739 --> 00:46:05,698
Can you please tell
Dr. Bensley

701
00:46:05,743 --> 00:46:07,734
that...

702
00:46:09,447 --> 00:46:13,110
he can just do whatever needs to do,
all right?

703
00:46:40,344 --> 00:46:42,335
Mary's behavior
is definitely indicative

704
00:46:42,379 --> 00:46:45,371
of someone in the midst
of an emotional breakdown.

705
00:46:45,416 --> 00:46:48,112
And yet I never met anyone
with such conviction

706
00:46:48,152 --> 00:46:50,450
in her delusion.

707
00:46:50,488 --> 00:46:53,321
She absolutely believes that everything
that's happening is real.

708
00:46:54,792 --> 00:46:57,886
She's emotionally lost.

709
00:47:05,703 --> 00:47:07,261
Yeah, this Bensley.

710
00:47:07,304 --> 00:47:10,899
Listen, I wanna put Mary Walsh
under 72-hour observation.

711
00:47:12,076 --> 00:47:15,307
Mm-hmm.
Possible mental illness.

712
00:47:43,607 --> 00:47:47,304
Mr. Holloway,
this is J.J.

713
00:47:47,344 --> 00:47:48,641
I have her
in the hallway.

714
00:47:48,679 --> 00:47:50,874
Switching to camera 2.

715
00:47:50,915 --> 00:47:53,577
I'm following her
along the hallway.

716
00:47:54,952 --> 00:47:57,182
I have her.
- Do not lose her.

717
00:47:57,221 --> 00:48:00,622
Sir, it looks like she's heading towards
sublevel "B"- boiler room and laundry.

718
00:48:00,658 --> 00:48:02,819
We only have limited
coverage down there.

719
00:48:02,860 --> 00:48:05,590
I'm en route right now.

720
00:48:56,280 --> 00:48:57,838
Dr. Bensley, what are
we dealing with here?

721
00:48:57,881 --> 00:48:59,405
Is she dangerous?

722
00:48:59,450 --> 00:49:01,077
It's impossible to say.

723
00:49:01,118 --> 00:49:03,985
Acute perception
of persecution, paranoia.

724
00:49:04,021 --> 00:49:06,888
You just never know
how someone like this will act

725
00:49:06,924 --> 00:49:09,119
when pushed too far.

726
00:49:14,698 --> 00:49:18,634
No, no.
No cameras, none.

727
00:49:18,669 --> 00:49:21,433
No parking lot.
No exits.

728
00:49:21,472 --> 00:49:23,337
No. I can't find
her anywhere.

729
00:49:23,374 --> 00:49:25,535
We only got a couple of cameras
operational in that area,

730
00:49:25,576 --> 00:49:27,771
so it's not gonna be easy.
I'm gonna keep on scanning.

731
00:49:27,811 --> 00:49:29,779
Wait, I think
I've got something.

732
00:49:29,813 --> 00:49:32,475
Boom! Camera 4 in the boiler room.
She's wearing blue scrubs.

733
00:49:32,516 --> 00:49:34,484
It looks like she's heading
towards the morgue.

734
00:49:34,518 --> 00:49:36,952
She's running. She's on the move.
I'm gonna lose her.

735
00:50:01,178 --> 00:50:03,703
You had a chance to talk with her.
Is she currently on meds?

736
00:50:03,747 --> 00:50:05,681
Yeah, quite
a potent dosage.

737
00:50:05,716 --> 00:50:08,913
Okay, so this could be some sort
of psychotic reaction.

738
00:50:08,952 --> 00:50:11,147
It could indeed.

739
00:50:18,996 --> 00:50:20,964
Hello.

740
00:50:20,998 --> 00:50:24,866
Kevin:
Hello, it's me.

741
00:50:24,902 --> 00:50:27,268
My God, Kevin.

742
00:50:27,304 --> 00:50:29,329
Where are you?

743
00:50:29,373 --> 00:50:31,898
I don't know.
Somewhere in the hospital.

744
00:50:33,477 --> 00:50:35,377
What's happening?

745
00:50:35,412 --> 00:50:37,539
Listen to me, okay?

746
00:50:37,581 --> 00:50:40,049
Don't trust anyone.

747
00:50:40,084 --> 00:50:42,143
I don't know how many people
are involved in this.

748
00:50:42,186 --> 00:50:43,847
It's very important,
okay?

749
00:50:43,887 --> 00:50:46,720
- What do they want?
- I don't know.

750
00:50:46,757 --> 00:50:50,158
She has to be close by.
She couldn't have gone too far.

751
00:50:50,194 --> 00:50:53,357
Check all the rooms
on that wing.

752
00:50:53,397 --> 00:50:55,831
Look around you. Where are you?
Where are you right now?

753
00:50:55,866 --> 00:50:58,061
I'm in a bathroom
somewhere.

754
00:50:58,102 --> 00:50:59,729
Are you okay?
Are you safe?

