760
00:51:15,886 --> 00:51:18,548
Kevin.

761
00:51:18,589 --> 00:51:22,025
Kevin. Kevin!

762
00:51:22,059 --> 00:51:24,254
Kevin.

763
00:51:34,571 --> 00:51:36,562
Miss Walsh.

764
00:51:38,075 --> 00:51:40,805
Miss Walsh, you in here?

765
00:52:29,726 --> 00:52:32,627
I got her. She's heading
towards the parking garage.

766
00:52:47,311 --> 00:52:49,370
Oh my God! Oh my God!
Are you all right?

767
00:52:49,413 --> 00:52:51,813
Are you all right?

768
00:52:51,849 --> 00:52:54,317
This is a first date.

769
00:52:54,351 --> 00:52:56,876
- We don't kiss on the first date.
- Third. Fifth date.

770
00:53:47,905 --> 00:53:49,964
Gonna wait?
This could take awhile.

771
00:53:54,878 --> 00:53:56,903
I think I've done
all I can do.

772
00:53:56,947 --> 00:54:00,110
Sorry she sent you
on such a wild goose chase.

773
00:54:00,150 --> 00:54:03,779
Yeah, it happens.

774
00:54:05,689 --> 00:54:08,214
- Good afternoon, Doc.
- Detective.

775
00:54:41,124 --> 00:54:43,115
Cooper: Hi, Mary.

776
00:54:44,828 --> 00:54:47,058
- Hello.
- Shh.

777
00:54:48,398 --> 00:54:51,367
I heard what happened.
These are for you.

778
00:54:53,704 --> 00:54:56,502
Hey, it's gonna be okay.

779
00:54:56,540 --> 00:54:59,338
The doctor thought you needed
some more time to recuperate.

780
00:54:59,376 --> 00:55:02,106
The cop- I think
he might have left.

781
00:55:02,145 --> 00:55:04,238
Thank you.

782
00:55:08,819 --> 00:55:10,787
They think I'm crazy.

783
00:55:10,821 --> 00:55:12,516
I'm not.

784
00:55:12,556 --> 00:55:14,148
I'm not crazy.

785
00:55:14,191 --> 00:55:17,683
No, you're not crazy.
That's why I came down here.

786
00:55:17,728 --> 00:55:19,923
I want to discuss the situation
about Kevin

787
00:55:19,963 --> 00:55:21,931
and how you could
see him again.

788
00:55:21,965 --> 00:55:23,592
You do wanna see
him again, right?

789
00:55:23,634 --> 00:55:25,101
Do you know
where he is?

790
00:55:25,135 --> 00:55:27,660
Now don't get yourself
worked up, young lady.

791
00:55:30,007 --> 00:55:32,908
You did make quite a spectacle
of yourself, Miss Walsh.

792
00:55:32,943 --> 00:55:35,673
The emotional outburst,
the panicking.

793
00:55:35,712 --> 00:55:38,806
We expected that,
but the accident.

794
00:55:38,849 --> 00:55:42,046
Oh, my my, Mary, I mean,
you've got to be more careful.

795
00:55:45,555 --> 00:55:49,514
"Mary Catherine Walsh, unmarried,
regional operations manager

796
00:55:49,559 --> 00:55:51,652
for the Empyrean
International Bank. "

797
00:55:51,695 --> 00:55:55,062
You rent a condo in Reseda.
Your mother died four months ago,

798
00:55:55,098 --> 00:55:58,192
but the bank got your house
in the reverse mortgage.

799
00:55:58,235 --> 00:56:00,863
That's true.

800
00:56:00,904 --> 00:56:04,465
- How do you know this?
- I did my research.

801
00:56:04,508 --> 00:56:06,066
But your bank,
on the other hand,

802
00:56:06,109 --> 00:56:08,407
recently received
from the federal government

803
00:56:08,445 --> 00:56:10,379
a $2 billion bailout.

804
00:56:10,414 --> 00:56:12,939
Now I've seen
the bonus structure,

805
00:56:12,983 --> 00:56:14,883
rewarding
their executives

806
00:56:14,918 --> 00:56:18,081
while letting their customers
go bankrupt, huh?

807
00:56:18,121 --> 00:56:22,114
And you have access
to unlimited funds.

808
00:56:27,064 --> 00:56:30,659
Don't you hurt him.
Don't you hurt him!

809
00:56:34,104 --> 00:56:36,095
So...

810
00:56:37,574 --> 00:56:40,168
- How much?
- $10 million.

811
00:56:40,210 --> 00:56:43,179
I've taken the liberty
to get Kevin's computer.

812
00:56:43,213 --> 00:56:46,774
Inside here you'll find the account
and wire routing numbers

813
00:56:46,817 --> 00:56:48,717
of a bank account
in the Cayman Islands.

814
00:56:48,752 --> 00:56:50,879
Once I receive confirmation
of funds received,

815
00:56:50,921 --> 00:56:53,446
I'll let your boyfriend go.

816
00:56:58,729 --> 00:57:00,754
Shit.

817
00:57:04,768 --> 00:57:06,395
I have no Wi-Fi signal.

818
00:57:06,436 --> 00:57:08,097
I checked it myself.
It's fine.

819
00:57:08,138 --> 00:57:10,072
Yeah, I don't have a wireless signal
in this room.

820
00:57:10,107 --> 00:57:11,972
I need a hard line.

821
00:57:12,008 --> 00:57:15,205
I need to move
to a different location.

822
00:57:15,245 --> 00:57:17,509
Yeah, it's me.

823
00:57:17,547 --> 00:57:19,242
Yeah, cut off
Peterson's finger.

824
00:57:19,282 --> 00:57:22,217
No, wait! Wait!
Tell him no.

825
00:57:22,252 --> 00:57:24,618
Look at this right here.

826
00:57:24,654 --> 00:57:27,521
This is our signal.
There is none.

827
00:57:27,557 --> 00:57:30,685
I've tried every
single network,

828
00:57:30,727 --> 00:57:33,218
- and there's nothing.
- Hold that for one second.

829
00:57:33,263 --> 00:57:35,731
I need you to move me
to a place

830
00:57:35,766 --> 00:57:38,166
where I can plug in
a different computer.

831
00:57:38,201 --> 00:57:39,998
I can get it done
in no time, okay?

832
00:57:40,036 --> 00:57:43,995
Yeah, all right.

833
00:57:44,040 --> 00:57:46,338
I've got 26 minutes till the cutoff,
which is exactly how much time

834
00:57:46,376 --> 00:57:49,504
you've got to find a computer
to get me my money.

835
00:57:49,546 --> 00:57:51,639
You're being watched.
We know everything you do.

836
00:57:51,681 --> 00:57:54,343
If you fail, Kevin dies.

837
00:57:54,384 --> 00:57:56,352
If you tell anyone,
Kevin dies.

838
00:57:56,386 --> 00:57:59,219
If you leave the hospital,
Kevin dies.

839
00:58:00,490 --> 00:58:01,923
Got it.

840
00:58:01,958 --> 00:58:04,483
Here's your clothing.
I found it downstairs.

841
00:58:04,528 --> 00:58:08,020
Meet me on sublevel "B"
when you're done.

842
00:58:09,866 --> 00:58:11,629
Wonderful.

843
00:58:56,112 --> 00:58:58,103
Miss Walsh?

844
00:59:31,147 --> 00:59:34,378
Mr. Holloway, that crazy
Mary Walsh lady is back

845
00:59:34,417 --> 00:59:36,385
wandering the halls.

846
00:59:36,419 --> 00:59:38,387
She's looking for a patient
that does not appear to be in our system.

847
00:59:38,421 --> 00:59:40,389
She needs be escorted
out immediately.

848
00:59:40,423 --> 00:59:42,414
- I'll alert Miss Markham.
- Thank you.

849
01:00:16,660 --> 01:00:19,925
We have footage of Miss Walsh
in the trauma recovery room.

850
01:00:19,963 --> 01:00:21,931
J.J., punch up everything on level 3,
would you, please?

851
01:00:21,965 --> 01:00:23,626
- Thank you.
- You got it.

852
01:00:26,469 --> 01:00:29,302
- Holloway: There you go.
- I wanted somebody on that door.

853
01:00:29,339 --> 01:00:31,307
Unfortunately,
the nurse stepped away.

854
01:00:31,341 --> 01:00:33,332
You don't really think
she's dangerous, do you?

855
01:00:33,376 --> 01:00:35,344
I'm not taking
any chances.

856
01:00:35,378 --> 01:00:38,211
Besides, with her injuries,
her well-being is my responsibility.

857
01:00:38,248 --> 01:00:40,273
Trust me. She's still here,
and we will find her.

858
01:00:40,317 --> 01:00:42,842
I have my people turning
this place upside down.

859
01:00:42,886 --> 01:00:44,478
Well, let me know the minute
you hear anything.

860
01:00:44,521 --> 01:00:46,079
I'm going back upstairs.

861
01:00:46,122 --> 01:00:48,522
You got it, Miss Markham.
Thank you.

862
01:01:57,293 --> 01:01:59,056
$10 million.

863
01:02:03,566 --> 01:02:05,761
$10 million.

864
01:02:43,173 --> 01:02:44,800
Please work.

865
01:04:04,854 --> 01:04:07,482
Hello.

866
01:04:07,524 --> 01:04:09,617
Mary: Kevin.

867
01:04:09,659 --> 01:04:13,390
- Mary, Mary.
- Oh, Kevin.

868
01:04:15,398 --> 01:04:17,161
Are you hurt?

869
01:04:17,200 --> 01:04:18,690
He's fine.

870
01:04:18,735 --> 01:04:20,635
Let him go.

871
01:04:20,670 --> 01:04:24,071
- The receipt.
- I need to email a confirmation code

872
01:04:24,107 --> 01:04:25,904
to complete
the wire transfer.

873
01:04:25,942 --> 01:04:29,844
So I would suggest
that you let him go now.

874
01:04:50,466 --> 01:04:52,491
Move it!

875
01:04:54,637 --> 01:04:58,038
Honey.

876
01:04:58,074 --> 01:04:59,939
I thought I lost
you forever.

877
01:04:59,976 --> 01:05:01,603
The code, come on!

878
01:05:01,644 --> 01:05:04,272
Done.

879
01:05:04,314 --> 01:05:06,077
Come on, let's go
up those stairs.

880
01:05:06,115 --> 01:05:09,243
We could get away.
Just go right up those stairs.

881
01:05:16,659 --> 01:05:18,752
Well, I'm glad
you made it safely.

882
01:05:18,795 --> 01:05:20,262
I understand you're from Missouri.
Is that correct?

883
01:05:20,296 --> 01:05:21,422
Yeah, Kansas City.

884
01:05:21,464 --> 01:05:24,456
- Is that near St. Louis?
- Other side of the state.

885
01:05:24,500 --> 01:05:26,161
Excuse me one second.

886
01:05:26,202 --> 01:05:27,931
Royal Cayman Bank & Trust.
This is Barry.

887
01:05:27,971 --> 01:05:31,463
Yeah, Conyers.
Yeah, it's me.

888
01:05:31,507 --> 01:05:33,031
Did it go through?

889
01:05:33,076 --> 01:05:36,307
Yes, sir. As a matter of fact,
it's pending right now.

890
01:05:36,346 --> 01:05:38,871
We're on, guys.

891
01:05:38,915 --> 01:05:40,473
Thank you, Miss Walsh.

892
01:05:44,921 --> 01:05:46,548
Great work, baby.

893
01:05:46,589 --> 01:05:50,150
I mean, fantastic.

894
01:05:53,429 --> 01:05:55,659
Kevin: It's a good thing too.
Just in time,

895
01:05:55,698 --> 01:05:58,667
'cause this brace is really starting
to make my leg really stiff.

896
01:06:01,137 --> 01:06:03,105
Kevin,
what are you doing?

897
01:06:03,139 --> 01:06:06,165
Cooper: Haven't you been paying any
attention? There is no Kevin Peterson.

898
01:06:07,343 --> 01:06:09,106
Kevin.

899
01:06:11,314 --> 01:06:13,009
Oh my God.
Where are you?

900
01:06:13,049 --> 01:06:16,849
I don't know.
I'm in the hospital somewhere.

901
01:06:16,886 --> 01:06:18,854
Can you get down here?

902
01:06:18,888 --> 01:06:21,482
- No, no, leave me alone!
- Kevin.

903
01:06:22,992 --> 01:06:26,655
There is no...

904
01:06:26,696 --> 01:06:29,665
Kevin Peterson.

905
01:06:31,067 --> 01:06:33,968
Kevin, Kevin!

906
01:06:37,173 --> 01:06:38,197
Kevin.

907
01:06:42,178 --> 01:06:45,614
Don't you hurt him.
Don't you hurt him.

908
01:06:45,648 --> 01:06:47,115
Oh, my.

909
01:06:47,150 --> 01:06:50,278
So how much?

910
01:06:56,592 --> 01:06:59,026
Franklin: What about the nurse,

911
01:06:59,062 --> 01:07:01,121
this Amanda?

912
01:07:01,164 --> 01:07:03,530
- So you must be Kevin Peterson.
- Yeah.

913
01:07:03,566 --> 01:07:05,534
- I'm Amanda.
- Markham: We don't have anyone

914
01:07:05,568 --> 01:07:08,059
- by that name.
- See you in an hour.

915
01:07:09,105 --> 01:07:11,232
- Mary: Lovely nurse came in to prep him.
- What was the nurse's name?

916
01:07:11,274 --> 01:07:13,401
Mary: Uh, no...
Amanda.

917
01:07:13,443 --> 01:07:17,243
- My boyfriend is Kevin Peterson...
- Come here, come here.

918
01:07:17,280 --> 01:07:19,145
...and we can't find him.

919
01:07:19,182 --> 01:07:22,913
My wife,
she has breast cancer.

920
01:07:22,952 --> 01:07:25,887
Well, she's up in chemo.

921
01:07:25,922 --> 01:07:28,220
That's him
right there.

922
01:07:28,257 --> 01:07:31,055
Color accuracy is difficult to determine
with closed-circuit cameras.

923
01:07:31,094 --> 01:07:35,394
You know, Detective Franklin,
we have people here she can talk to.

924
01:07:35,431 --> 01:07:38,594
I'm sure Miss Markham could
arrange something, if need be.

925
01:07:38,634 --> 01:07:40,864
Mary:
Everything is a lie?

926
01:07:40,903 --> 01:07:43,201
Everything
is a lie?

927
01:07:43,239 --> 01:07:45,639
Every- every-
everything-

928
01:07:45,675 --> 01:07:49,611
- everything is a lie.
- Don't take it personally, Mare.

929
01:07:49,645 --> 01:07:52,375
- Mare bear.
- Don't touch me.

930
01:07:52,415 --> 01:07:54,576
The man you fell
in love with...

931
01:07:56,652 --> 01:07:58,415
he's not real.

932
01:07:58,454 --> 01:08:01,048
I'm a real idiot.

933
01:08:14,604 --> 01:08:17,937
Didn't he tell you about his time in prison?
That's where I met the guy.

934
01:08:17,974 --> 01:08:20,408
Believe me, if I was any younger,
I would have done this myself.

935
01:08:20,443 --> 01:08:23,537
No no no, Coop.
You couldn't handle her.

936
01:08:23,579 --> 01:08:26,104
She's a real tiger cat
between the sheets.

937
01:08:26,149 --> 01:08:28,743
Oh, I don't know, Coop.

938
01:08:28,785 --> 01:08:32,243
I think you could
have handled her.

939
01:08:33,856 --> 01:08:35,323
Holloway: All we had
to do was sit back

940
01:08:35,358 --> 01:08:38,088
and watch you lose it.
It was simple.

941
01:08:38,127 --> 01:08:41,494
Mare bear,
for old times' sake.

942
01:08:41,531 --> 01:08:44,125
- Come on in.
- Don't you dare touch me.

943
01:08:44,167 --> 01:08:46,727
- Don't touch me.
- Allow me.

944
01:08:46,769 --> 01:08:48,964
Boys, I think
it's time to go.

945
01:08:49,005 --> 01:08:51,906
All right, Holloway,
you know the drill.

946
01:08:51,941 --> 01:08:53,408
Amanda.

947
01:08:53,443 --> 01:08:55,775
I'll send you a postcard.

948
01:09:01,083 --> 01:09:03,313
I'm sorry.

949
01:09:14,197 --> 01:09:17,462
Victoria Markham's
office, please.

950
01:09:19,068 --> 01:09:22,094
It's Detective Franklin.
Tell her it's urgent.

951
01:09:22,138 --> 01:09:25,005
What do you mean she disappeared?
Where'd she go?

952
01:09:26,676 --> 01:09:29,702
Look, I think she's telling us the truth
about her boyfriend.

953
01:09:29,745 --> 01:09:31,713
She's messed up in something.
I don't know what it is.

954
01:09:31,747 --> 01:09:34,511
I think she's in some kind of trouble.
Just find her.

955
01:09:34,550 --> 01:09:37,144
Just find her!
I'm on my way there right now.

956
01:09:52,568 --> 01:09:55,059
Whoo!

957
01:09:55,104 --> 01:09:57,698
$10 million feels good,
doesn't it, babe?

958
01:09:57,740 --> 01:09:59,332
Baby, gimme a kiss.

959
01:10:15,424 --> 01:10:18,689
You know,
I almost feel bad.

960
01:10:18,728 --> 01:10:21,253
Amanda:
Oh, yeah, why is that?

961
01:10:21,297 --> 01:10:25,290
Almost, but I can think of
10 million reasons why not.

962
01:10:26,469 --> 01:10:29,768
Come on! Up!

963
01:10:29,805 --> 01:10:31,739
Get up those stairs.
Come on!

964
01:10:31,774 --> 01:10:35,471
Don't fight me!

965
01:10:35,511 --> 01:10:38,878
Yeah, you're a fighter,
